SIMPLE: corallin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Corallin
<hw>Cor"al*lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named in
allusion to the color of red corallin, fr. L. <ets>corallum</ets>
coral.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A yellow coal-tar dyestuff which
probably consists chiefly of rosolic acid. See <er>Aurin</er>, and
<cref>Rosolic acid</cref> under <er>Rosolic</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Red corallin</b></col>, <cd>a red dyestuff which is
obtained by treating aurin or rosolic acid with ammonia; -- called also
<altname>p⟦ae⟧onin</altname>.</cd> -- <col><b>Yellow corallin</b></col>.
<cd>See <er>Aurin</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coralline</ent>⟦br⟧
